title: GAC names conference football players of the week
text:
GAC names conference football players of the week By -   
RUSSELLVILLE, Ark. (AP) - The Great American Conference has named Southern Arkansas’ Barrett Renner; Oklahoma Baptist’s Brynden Pitzer; and Southwestern Oklahoma State’s D.J. Jones the conference’s football players of the week. 
Renner is offensive Player of the Week after throwing five touchdowns, including the game-winning touchdown with 37 seconds to play, in SAU’s 32-28 win over Ouachita. 
Pitzer is defensive Player of the Week after recording nine tackles, 1½ quarterback sacks and returning an interception for a touchdown in Oklahoma Baptist’s win over Northwestern Oklahoma State. 
Jones is special teams Player of the Week after returning a punt 54 yards for a touchdown in SWOSU’s 73-7 win over Southern Nazarene. Jones also caught two touchdown passes.
